WEBVTT

00:02.086 --> 00:03.806
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.838 --> 00:05.840
I know what you're going through.
Go to art school.

00:06.007 --> 00:08.175
Find the life you want. Don't look back.

00:08.342 --> 00:09.802
ENZO:
Meet the real Sarah Salvatore.

00:09.969 --> 00:12.930
Stefan set me up to die,
which resulted in days of torture.

00:13.097 --> 00:16.100
I started plotting my revenge.
I'm going to make her do things...

00:16.308 --> 00:19.979
...she had never dreamed of doing
until she begs me to make her a vampire.

00:20.187 --> 00:22.356
DAMON:
Liz and I are pretty close.

00:22.523 --> 00:23.899
FORBES:
I need you to promise me something.

00:24.108 --> 00:27.570
When I'm gone, Caroline is gonna need you
to help her move on with her life.

00:27.737 --> 00:30.823
- Promise me that you will do that, Stefan.
STEFAN: Promise.

00:35.411 --> 00:37.121
Hey, Tony, I'm headed home.

00:37.288 --> 00:39.608
Could you do me a favor
and check up on the Lockwood place?

00:39.707 --> 00:42.793
Carol called, again.
Another five-martini stalker sighting.

00:42.960 --> 00:46.338
Oh, and some teenagers
are planning a bonfire off Route 13.

00:46.505 --> 00:49.633
No one's called to complain yet,
but they will. See you.

00:49.800 --> 00:51.802
[PHONE RINGING]

01:04.315 --> 01:05.858
Forbes.

01:08.319 --> 01:10.071
I'll be right there.

01:10.237 --> 01:12.239
[SIRENS WAILING]

01:14.784 --> 01:15.868
Hey, what happened?

01:16.035 --> 01:19.080
Accident up at Wickery Bridge.
Driver lost control, careened off.

01:19.246 --> 01:20.414
- Any other casualties?
- Two.

01:20.581 --> 01:22.792
- Survivors?
- One. We found her, unconscious.

01:22.958 --> 01:25.461
She must have crawled out of the car
and passed out.

01:27.922 --> 01:29.590
Elena Gilbert.

01:30.216 --> 01:33.427
Where's her brother?
Who were the casualties?

01:33.594 --> 01:35.638
Miranda and Grayson. Her parents.

02:25.688 --> 02:26.981
<i>Principal Weber...</i>

02:27.356 --> 02:29.483
...I know that graduation
isn't for a few months...

02:29.650 --> 02:32.778
...but Jeremy just got accepted
into this great art school.

02:32.945 --> 02:35.114
Jeremy Gilbert? I don't think so.

02:35.281 --> 02:36.782
Not with his academic record.

02:36.949 --> 02:38.617
- What's wrong?
- You have a few hours?

02:38.784 --> 02:41.537
All right, let's start with drug use
in his freshman year.

02:41.704 --> 02:44.123
- You mean the year that his parents died?
- Okay.

02:44.290 --> 02:48.460
So, what's the excuse for the next
three years of woeful attendance?

02:48.627 --> 02:51.922
Extracurricular activities,
health and fitness, that sort of thing.

02:52.089 --> 02:54.633
- I mean, you see how scrawny he used to be?
- No.

02:54.800 --> 02:57.219
But I do recall the four months
where he faked his death.

02:57.386 --> 02:59.263
Funny thing, he actually didn't fake it.

02:59.430 --> 03:01.098
We went to this island
off the coast of Canada...

03:01.265 --> 03:03.184
...in search of this cure
for vampirism, and...

03:03.350 --> 03:05.436
- Damon.
- Is this some sort of joke to you?

03:05.603 --> 03:10.399
No. Look, Jeremy has had a rough time here.
I know, but that's part of the reason...

03:10.566 --> 03:12.693
- ...why we want him to go.
- Yeah.

03:14.403 --> 03:16.488
Well, I'm sorry, but I
can't let that happen.

03:16.655 --> 03:19.992
- So can we try this my way now?
- We already compelled him into art school.

03:20.159 --> 03:22.494
Sorry that I wanted my brother
to actually get a degree.

03:22.661 --> 03:26.332
He will. He just won't earn it. Okay.

03:26.498 --> 03:28.125
Uh, ahem.

03:30.294 --> 03:34.089
This small-town atmosphere doesn't nurture
a creative spirit like Jeremy Gilbert.

03:34.256 --> 03:39.220
And it's of your opinion that it's high time
for him to get the hell out of Mystic Falls.

03:44.266 --> 03:47.561
To Matt's phone, which is more important
than my last day in town.

03:47.728 --> 03:50.481
- I'm here. Where's Tyler?
- He broke up with his girlfriend.

03:50.648 --> 03:53.442
He gets a free pass.
Look, I wanna take this shot...

03:53.609 --> 03:55.736
...before Alaric changes his mind.

03:55.903 --> 03:58.864
This place is closed for another hour.
I'm making an exception.

03:59.240 --> 04:00.532
Cheers.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.409
- Cheers.
- To you, brother.

04:05.371 --> 04:08.666
I swear, Jeremy, if I get a call
from the drunk tank in Santa Fe...

04:08.832 --> 04:11.669
You're gonna make your girlfriend
give me an STD test again?

04:12.044 --> 04:14.129
That cleared up, right?

04:16.298 --> 04:18.300
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

04:20.928 --> 04:23.055
Why is Enzo alive
and why is he calling you?

04:23.222 --> 04:25.391
Nothing you need to worry about.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.394
Hey. It's Jeremy's going-away party.

04:28.560 --> 04:31.063
- Whatever you want, it can wait.
ENZO: <i>Actually, it can't.</i>

04:31.230 --> 04:33.357
Don't worry,
I'm not sending you back to Duke.

04:33.524 --> 04:36.402
- I brought Duke to you.
- What the hell does that...?

04:36.568 --> 04:40.739
I take it from your abrupt pause that you
either had a small stroke or Sarah walked in.

04:40.906 --> 04:43.409
<i>Good news either way.
Make her feel welcome.</i>

04:43.575 --> 04:47.413
Oh, and, uh, don't go blabbing details
of our little arrangement around the party.

04:47.579 --> 04:50.874
<i>Your tongue functions
much better inside your mouth.</i>

04:51.333 --> 04:53.419
- Matt.
- Hey. What are you doing here?

04:53.585 --> 04:55.421
I got a call from the
manager of this place.

04:55.587 --> 04:58.757
He needed someone to take pictures,
and he said you mentioned me.

04:59.341 --> 05:02.094
I mean, normally the pictures I take
are a little darker...

05:02.261 --> 05:06.181
- ...but normally I don't get paid, so thanks.
- You're welcome.

05:06.890 --> 05:09.393
- You wanna show me around?
- Yeah, yeah.

05:20.070 --> 05:21.613
- O h!
- Look who graduated.

05:25.451 --> 05:27.536
- He was okay with it?
- Sure. I mean...

05:27.703 --> 05:30.622
...practically flunking,
missed a hundred days of school...

05:30.789 --> 05:34.209
...and you can barely spell "cat,"
but he was fine with you graduating early.

05:34.376 --> 05:37.463
We helped the process along.

05:37.629 --> 05:38.922
Mm-hm.

05:40.591 --> 05:41.800
I'm gonna get a drink.

05:43.218 --> 05:44.428
[SIGHS]

05:44.595 --> 05:47.014
- Is she okay?
- She will be.

05:47.639 --> 05:52.144
We all will. Somehow we'll all find a way
to move on without you, Jeremy.

05:52.853 --> 05:55.147
Oh, hey, just did.

05:55.564 --> 05:56.815
Oh, look under the cap...

05:56.982 --> 06:00.319
...I jacked a little going-away present
from Ric's girlfriend's stash.

06:03.197 --> 06:04.531
Put it away, you idiot.

06:07.659 --> 06:10.496
Tell your sister, I'll kill you. Again.

06:23.092 --> 06:26.261
CAROLINE: If you really think about it,
Jeremy leaving is for the best.

06:26.428 --> 06:28.680
I'm sure everything around him
reminds him of Bonnie.

06:28.847 --> 06:31.517
Elena's always wanted to protect him
from vampire drama.

06:31.975 --> 06:35.145
Granted, he is going to art school,
where the percentage rate...

06:35.312 --> 06:39.191
...for a well-paying job is one of the
lowest, but I really am happy for him.

06:39.358 --> 06:41.527
Do you think you packed enough?

06:41.693 --> 06:45.531
The whole point of this is for my mom
to live out the rest of her time here...

06:45.697 --> 06:49.034
...in a relaxed and peaceful environment
surrounded by the things she loves.

06:49.201 --> 06:52.037
Like photo albums and board games.

06:52.204 --> 06:55.666
<i>"The Anthology of Shakespeare</i>
Volumes 1 through 12"?

06:55.833 --> 06:58.210
All the books that she's
never gotten around to reading.

06:58.377 --> 06:59.545
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

06:59.711 --> 07:01.630
Oh, hey, uh,
do you mind just getting that?

07:01.797 --> 07:02.881
Oh.

07:03.048 --> 07:04.967
- Get...? Um...
- Yeah. Um, okay.

07:05.134 --> 07:06.844
Um...

07:07.010 --> 07:08.470
- Sorry.
- Yeah, it's okay.

07:10.347 --> 07:12.099
Got it. Um...

07:13.267 --> 07:14.643
Why is my mom calling you?

07:16.061 --> 07:17.896
Are you going behind my back
for information?

07:18.063 --> 07:20.566
Well, hello, Stefan.
What a lovely voice you have.

07:20.732 --> 07:22.067
Why are you calling him?

07:22.234 --> 07:24.903
You snuck out of the house
without so much as a hello.

07:25.070 --> 07:28.323
I may be a retired sheriff,
but I'm still a mother. What are you up to?

07:28.490 --> 07:30.659
CAROLINE:
If I told you, it would ruin the surprise.

07:30.826 --> 07:31.910
Master bedroom.

07:32.286 --> 07:35.581
At least tell me if Stefan is there
voluntarily or against his will.

07:35.747 --> 07:38.876
Neither. He's here because
you asked him to look after me.

07:39.042 --> 07:42.379
- Sweetheart, that's not true.
- I heard you talking to him in the hospital.

07:42.546 --> 07:44.840
You asked him to look after me
and make me smile...

07:45.007 --> 07:49.928
<i>...and help me move on with my life
after you're gone.</i>

07:50.095 --> 07:52.306
I'm sure that's not
the only reason he's there.

07:52.473 --> 07:54.683
Mom, look, it's okay.

07:54.850 --> 07:59.021
Needed an extra set of hands anyway. I will
call you in three hours with all the details.

07:59.188 --> 08:01.064
Until then, no cheating. I love you.

08:05.569 --> 08:06.945
[SIGHS]

08:09.156 --> 08:10.616
Not to be blunt...

08:11.033 --> 08:13.911
...but I think dying
gets you a ticket out of work.

08:14.661 --> 08:16.747
- Heh.
- Just saying.

08:21.960 --> 08:23.420
How are you feeling?

08:23.587 --> 08:26.798
Like I'm not gonna leave this job
with unfinished business.

08:27.090 --> 08:28.717
I have all these open cases.

08:29.676 --> 08:32.804
Well, let me see if I can help you close
a couple of them.

08:33.804 --> 08:36.140
Aw. Yeah.

08:40.979 --> 08:42.606
This one was me.

08:44.316 --> 08:45.651
Me.

08:46.818 --> 08:48.695
Also me.

08:49.196 --> 08:51.907
Ooh. This one was Stefan's.

08:52.074 --> 08:54.576
Oh, wait. No, me.

08:55.202 --> 08:58.247
Yeah. I always had a sneaking suspicion.

08:59.289 --> 09:00.499
What about this one?

09:02.501 --> 09:06.421
Elena's parents. I didn't know
there was an open investigation.

09:07.172 --> 09:09.508
At the time, I was taking care
of Elena and Jeremy...

09:09.675 --> 09:12.094
...and I didn't wanna drag them
through more heartache.

09:12.261 --> 09:16.098
And then when I was finally ready
to reopen the wound, Elena had moved on...

09:16.265 --> 09:21.687
...and you and I had become friends,
and I worried that...

09:23.981 --> 09:26.858
What? That I was involved?

09:28.068 --> 09:29.152
Liz, no.

09:29.653 --> 09:31.697
No, I promise you.

09:33.865 --> 09:35.367
[SIGHS]

09:37.369 --> 09:41.456
Miranda left me this message
two hours before they got in that car.

09:41.623 --> 09:44.209
Two hours before they drove off that road
for no reason.

09:44.710 --> 09:46.295
RECORDING:
<i>Liz, it's Miranda Gilbert.</i>

09:46.461 --> 09:50.716
<i>I have something urgent to talk to you about.
Please, call me back as soon as you can.</i>

09:50.882 --> 09:52.926
Well, I'll be damned.

09:54.052 --> 09:58.473
Looks like you've got a good old-fashioned
sheriffy whodunit on your hands.

10:12.654 --> 10:15.032
ELENA:
You know I'm a vampire, right?

10:15.198 --> 10:17.409
A big sister with nearly perfect senses...

10:17.576 --> 10:19.953
...who can sneak up on you
without making a sound.

10:20.454 --> 10:21.663
Really sucks for you.

10:22.414 --> 10:23.915
- Give it.
- Damon gave it to me.

10:24.082 --> 10:26.418
Technically,
it's from Ric's girlfriend's stash.

10:26.585 --> 10:30.505
Damon's an idiot and Alaric conveniently
disappeared, so I can only yell at you.

10:32.049 --> 10:35.218
Yeah, Ric left. He was worried
someone might recognize him...

10:35.385 --> 10:37.512
...when he's supposed to be dead.

10:37.679 --> 10:40.098
Right. That hadn't occurred to me.

10:40.932 --> 10:42.351
[ELENA CHUCKLES]

10:42.517 --> 10:46.021
- Our lives are so weird.
- That's the understatement of the century.

10:51.068 --> 10:53.904
- Give me your lighter.
- Really?

10:55.030 --> 11:00.285
Yes. I just decided that me
smoking a joint with my little brother...

11:00.452 --> 11:03.705
...might be the most normal thing
that we've done together in years.

11:07.751 --> 11:11.129
Look what I found in the...

11:15.717 --> 11:19.262
You know, if you're gonna go for a spin,
I suggest you, uh, get your helmet.

11:19.429 --> 11:22.641
Heh. This is the bike
that I learned to ride on.

11:22.808 --> 11:24.810
I just didn't know my mom kept it.

11:24.976 --> 11:28.939
It used to have training wheels with lights
that would flash every time you pedaled.

11:29.106 --> 11:32.401
One day, my mom took them off
and said it was time to be a big girl.

11:32.567 --> 11:36.613
You can imagine the princess-sized tantrum
that followed.

11:36.780 --> 11:39.658
Well, they had lights. I don't blame you.

11:39.825 --> 11:41.118
Yeah.

11:41.284 --> 11:44.579
So, what's with all this?

11:44.746 --> 11:48.375
Well, the box was loose
so I figured I would fix it.

11:49.334 --> 11:51.461
You know that you don't have
to do all this, right?

11:51.628 --> 11:55.841
Actually, you could have had some serious
problems. Exposed wires, electrical fires.

11:56.007 --> 11:59.761
No, I mean being here with me. Heh.

11:59.928 --> 12:03.557
- If you have someplace else you'd rather be...
- I don't.

12:14.776 --> 12:16.695
[FORBES SIGHS]

12:18.155 --> 12:21.283
You know, this would be
a lot more fun if I had...

12:21.450 --> 12:22.868
Top right-hand drawer.

12:26.788 --> 12:27.873
Well, look at that.

12:29.291 --> 12:31.793
This is why you are a terrible sheriff.

12:31.960 --> 12:33.378
No, I'm a terrible sheriff...

12:33.545 --> 12:37.507
...because one of my best friends
is the perp in half my open cases.

12:37.716 --> 12:40.010
- Not till I finish this.
- Suit yourself.

12:43.346 --> 12:45.056
Can I ask you something?

12:45.223 --> 12:46.558
About that night?

12:46.933 --> 12:50.061
You saw Elena,
and Stefan pulled her out of the car.

12:50.228 --> 12:53.064
Yeah, Stefan, always a one-upper.

12:53.231 --> 12:57.068
So you both just happened to be in town
the night her parents died.

12:58.028 --> 12:59.112
Why?

12:59.279 --> 13:01.907
Well, believe it or not, Liz,
I once had a mommy too.

13:02.073 --> 13:05.660
She died around that day. And the years
when my emotions were "on"...

13:05.827 --> 13:08.997
...I would stop by
and lay flowers at her grave.

13:11.500 --> 13:12.876
You never talk about her.

13:13.794 --> 13:16.087
Not much to say. She died.

13:16.254 --> 13:17.839
Old-timey disease.

13:18.006 --> 13:19.090
Consumption.

13:19.883 --> 13:22.093
Why do I feel like
you're leaving something out?

13:23.053 --> 13:27.390
Tell you what, why don't we use
your investigative instincts to solve this?

13:27.557 --> 13:29.559
Come here, check this out.

13:30.560 --> 13:34.773
All right, so why were the Gilberts
taking Wickery Bridge...

13:34.940 --> 13:37.776
...when Old Miller Road
was clearly 10 minutes faster...

13:38.151 --> 13:39.945
...and why are there
no skid marks at the scene...

13:40.111 --> 13:43.698
...and why was the trunk full of luggage
as if they were going out of town?

13:44.866 --> 13:47.327
Something did happen that night.

13:48.078 --> 13:50.622
- Let me have your car.
- No way in hell.

13:51.289 --> 13:55.377
Come on, I'm moving to a new town,
starting a new life. I need a car.

13:55.544 --> 13:56.628
And it has to be mine?

13:58.088 --> 14:00.131
Just compel yourself a new one.

14:00.507 --> 14:03.885
Heh. How many cars do you think
we've destroyed?

14:04.052 --> 14:06.471
Like, more than the average family, right?

14:06.638 --> 14:09.641
- Mom and Dad's station wagon. That's one.
- The SUV I got for my birthday.

14:09.808 --> 14:12.769
Katherine wrapped my car
around a light post. That's three.

14:12.936 --> 14:15.230
They really didn't give us many fries,
did they?

14:15.397 --> 14:17.899
Yeah, they did. You just ate them all.

14:18.108 --> 14:20.110
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

14:23.280 --> 14:25.490
Oh, my God. We're so busted.

14:25.657 --> 14:26.992
Dude, just click ignore.

14:27.158 --> 14:28.618
Dude, I am.

14:28.785 --> 14:32.289
[ELENA LAUGHS, THEN GROANS]

14:33.206 --> 14:34.332
It's official.

14:34.708 --> 14:36.835
I am the world's worst sister.

14:37.002 --> 14:39.588
- Don't be stupid.
- I am.

14:40.463 --> 14:42.883
Mom and Dad died and what did I do?

14:43.717 --> 14:47.137
I let you be Jenna's problem
because I couldn't deal.

14:48.555 --> 14:49.681
I shut you out.

14:51.391 --> 14:53.476
I shut everybody out.

14:55.478 --> 14:57.772
Well, I never thought
that made you a bad sister.

14:57.939 --> 15:01.192
If anything, it was nice to have someone
to go through it with.

15:01.943 --> 15:05.864
When you got better,
that's when I felt the most alone.

15:06.031 --> 15:08.366
That wasn't your fault. You were healing.

15:08.533 --> 15:09.784
I wasn't.

15:12.120 --> 15:14.122
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

15:14.956 --> 15:19.461
- What, Damon? I'm bonding with my brother.
DAMON: <i>I wanted to run something by you.</i>

15:20.253 --> 15:22.756
Is there any chance
you can get to the sheriff's office?

15:22.923 --> 15:24.132
Um...

15:24.299 --> 15:27.344
Not so sure it's a good idea
to be around the sheriff right now.

15:27.510 --> 15:28.637
[CHUCKLES]

15:28.803 --> 15:32.182
Jeremy and I smoked
your going-away present.

15:32.891 --> 15:36.811
- Are you stoned?
- No. I'm lightly buzzed.

15:37.896 --> 15:42.400
Ah. Okay, well, you need some eyedrops,
a squirt of perfume and half a pizza.

15:42.567 --> 15:43.735
This is important.

15:44.194 --> 15:46.655
Okay, I'll walk over now.

15:48.406 --> 15:51.409
Whew. Hide the evidence.
See you at home.

15:51.952 --> 15:53.703
[ELENA GRUNTS]

15:55.538 --> 15:58.917
What is that strange smell?

15:59.834 --> 16:01.878
So I hear you're leaving town.

16:02.045 --> 16:07.926
Probably smart considering you tried
to kill me and, surprise, I'm still here.

16:10.470 --> 16:12.973
So we can go moodier
with the lighting if you want...

16:13.139 --> 16:15.141
...or feature more patrons or menu items.

16:15.308 --> 16:18.687
No, these are great. I'll send these
over to my manager. Whoa.

16:18.853 --> 16:21.356
- Too far.
- Oh, my God. Heh.

16:22.023 --> 16:23.692
Totally forgot that was on there.

16:24.317 --> 16:26.569
Anyone ever tell you
you're a really good photographer?

16:26.736 --> 16:30.156
- Yeah, but obviously I didn't take that one.
- Who did?

16:30.949 --> 16:34.452
Uh, whoa. Never mind.
That's none of my business. Uh...

16:34.619 --> 16:36.913
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

16:40.875 --> 16:43.628
This is gonna come as a shock to you,
but this is not a good time.

16:43.795 --> 16:46.256
This will come as a shock to you,
but I don't care.

16:46.423 --> 16:48.967
There's a tunnel along the river,
off Route 13.

16:49.134 --> 16:52.303
Dark, private. I want you to bring
our photographer friend there.

16:54.180 --> 16:56.599
- What are you gonna do to her?
- Shake her hand...

16:56.766 --> 16:59.811
...exchange pleasantries,
standard introductory behavior.

16:59.978 --> 17:01.312
If you wanna meet her, come here.

17:01.604 --> 17:03.940
See, that sounded
like you telling me what to do.

17:04.107 --> 17:07.318
Is this the part where you threaten
my mom again? Because that's brave.

17:07.652 --> 17:09.988
Yeah, you're right. That was uncalled for.

17:10.155 --> 17:12.365
After all, what has your mom
ever done to me?

17:12.531 --> 17:13.950
Well, besides that one night.

17:14.117 --> 17:16.618
- I'm hanging up now.
- So I went with something local.

17:16.786 --> 17:18.997
That's more noble. Right, Jeremy?

17:19.164 --> 17:21.082
[MUFFLED CRY]

17:22.500 --> 17:26.337
He's trying to say something.
It's a bit garbled with all the blood.

17:26.503 --> 17:28.965
Oh, there, he said: ungh.

17:29.132 --> 17:30.341
What the hell did you do?

17:31.551 --> 17:33.344
Nothing too serious. Yet.

17:33.511 --> 17:35.847
So care to reconsider my request?

17:49.194 --> 17:52.697
Hey, so, uh, you brought
an entire crate of these.

17:52.864 --> 17:54.616
Any idea where I should store them?

17:54.783 --> 17:57.118
There's, uh, a cellar under the stairs.

18:02.040 --> 18:03.708
You okay?

18:04.167 --> 18:07.879
You realize whichever book my mom reaches
for could be the last thing she reads?

18:08.963 --> 18:11.800
<i>Jane Eyre</i> is 600 pages.

18:11.966 --> 18:13.426
What if she doesn't finish?

18:13.593 --> 18:16.930
What if she gets halfway through
and then realizes that she hates it?

18:17.097 --> 18:20.767
What if she wastes her final
precious moments on a terrible book?

18:20.934 --> 18:24.479
I don't wanna be held responsible
for ruining her last literary experience.

18:24.646 --> 18:27.148
- Caroline.
- Yeah?

18:27.690 --> 18:29.567
Let me deal with the books.

18:29.734 --> 18:31.361
No. No, I should do it.

18:31.528 --> 18:34.072
I have probably read
every single one of these.

18:35.031 --> 18:37.408
I'm happy to take the responsibility.

18:38.868 --> 18:40.286
[SIGHS]

18:43.206 --> 18:45.250
I'm opening this.

18:46.084 --> 18:48.211
- I thought that was for your mom.
- Oh, it was.

18:56.553 --> 18:59.097
Honestly, I don't remember
why we took that route home.

18:59.264 --> 19:01.683
And I had no idea
that there was luggage in the trunk.

19:01.850 --> 19:03.560
What about the lack of skid marks?

19:03.726 --> 19:05.562
Any reason your dad would just drive off...

19:05.728 --> 19:08.231
...like he was trying to avoid something
without braking?

19:08.398 --> 19:10.608
I was texting with Bonnie
when it happened.

19:11.025 --> 19:13.361
Embarrassing, I know.

19:13.528 --> 19:16.364
- What about the voice-mail?
- I wasn't home that night.

19:18.533 --> 19:21.452
You really think that there's something up
with my parents' crash?

19:21.953 --> 19:23.371
I don't know.

19:23.538 --> 19:26.624
But given the way this town works,
I wouldn't be surprised.

19:27.208 --> 19:28.418
[ELENA SIGHS]

19:28.585 --> 19:31.379
I'm so sorry, Elena. I know
I should have brought this up sooner...

19:31.546 --> 19:34.799
...but in those first few weeks
after your parents died, I...

19:34.966 --> 19:38.219
No. You took care of Jeremy and I.
I remember.

19:39.304 --> 19:41.890
Poor Jenna was trying and failing.

19:42.056 --> 19:43.308
[ELENA CHUCKLES]

19:43.474 --> 19:47.395
But you let us stay at your place,
you took us to school...

19:47.562 --> 19:48.897
- ...made us dinner.
- Wait.

19:50.064 --> 19:51.649
You cook?

19:52.650 --> 19:54.110
She really tried.

19:54.277 --> 19:56.571
[BOTH LAUGH]

20:00.575 --> 20:02.327
I'll see if Jeremy knows anything.

20:03.328 --> 20:05.455
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

20:07.081 --> 20:08.666
[ELENA SIGHS]

20:20.386 --> 20:22.347
Hey.

20:23.139 --> 20:24.224
You okay?

20:24.390 --> 20:26.351
Yup. Yup. I'm good.

20:26.517 --> 20:28.519
- Yeah?
- I'm fine.

20:28.686 --> 20:30.355
Okay.

20:31.648 --> 20:34.859
Sure, I'll follow a guy I barely know
into a shady tunnel.

20:35.026 --> 20:37.737
Hey, would you rather take more pictures
of potato skins?

20:37.904 --> 20:41.449
- I thought you were into dark subject matter.
- Graffiti.

20:41.616 --> 20:43.117
How provocative.

20:43.284 --> 20:47.080
This is Mystic Falls.
This is about as dark as it gets.

20:47.247 --> 20:48.873
[SARAH CHUCKLES]

20:57.382 --> 21:01.302
About those photos,
my roommate took them for her art final.

21:03.471 --> 21:06.349
I don't have a boyfriend,
if that's what you were wondering.

21:07.225 --> 21:09.227
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

21:13.398 --> 21:17.235
- All right, we're here. Where the hell are
you? ENZO: <i>I'm here. Can you not see me?</i>

21:17.402 --> 21:19.028
No. I can't.

21:19.195 --> 21:22.407
<i>Take a few steps to your left. Here I am.</i>

21:26.494 --> 21:27.912
Matt!

21:29.080 --> 21:30.832
[COUGHING]

21:39.424 --> 21:42.051
They're running a little late.
Apparently my mom chose today...

21:42.218 --> 21:44.595
...to tackle an entire career
worth of cold cases.

21:44.762 --> 21:46.014
STEFAN:
Hm.

21:46.431 --> 21:49.434
Well, they're gonna have a lot
of catching up to do.

21:52.603 --> 21:54.522
So, uh...

21:55.023 --> 21:57.859
...I realized that it doesn't matter.

21:58.401 --> 21:59.902
What doesn't matter?

22:00.737 --> 22:05.700
It doesn't matter what book your mom reads
in her final precious moments.

22:06.284 --> 22:10.121
It doesn't matter if it's
good or if it's terrible.

22:10.288 --> 22:15.251
It doesn't matter because life
isn't about your final moments.

22:15.960 --> 22:18.129
It's about the moments that led up to them.

22:23.801 --> 22:25.470
I know.

22:25.636 --> 22:28.222
I just wanted it to be perfect, you know?

22:28.389 --> 22:29.807
- I just wanted...
- Control?

22:32.560 --> 22:35.897
Hey, look, if anyone can control death...

22:38.441 --> 22:40.068
...it's you.

22:46.574 --> 22:48.659
I know that she asked you to look after me.

22:49.911 --> 22:52.413
- Caroline, that's not...
- And I'm okay with it.

22:52.580 --> 22:56.000
Really, I'm glad, actually...

22:56.501 --> 23:00.505
...because I don't know if I would be able
to get through this on my own.

23:02.507 --> 23:06.177
I'm not here because your mom
asked me to look after you.

23:07.970 --> 23:12.475
- Well, then why are you here?
- Well, because you're my friend.

23:14.185 --> 23:16.813
Because I know what it feels like
to lose a mother.

23:19.357 --> 23:24.862
And because when you told me
you hated me...

23:25.321 --> 23:29.325
...that was pretty much the worst thing
I had heard in a long time.

23:33.371 --> 23:36.707
I think we both know
I never really hated you.

24:29.260 --> 24:32.054
One of us should probably say something.

24:33.097 --> 24:34.765
Go for it.

24:36.100 --> 24:37.351
Not that.

24:43.858 --> 24:44.942
I called 911.

24:45.109 --> 24:46.777
You need to get out of here.

24:46.944 --> 24:50.072
What kind of person just barrels
into someone and then drives off?

24:50.239 --> 24:52.742
ENZO:
Are you okay? What happened?

24:52.909 --> 24:55.036
Do you need help?
I was walking and I heard you two.

24:55.203 --> 24:58.456
We're waiting for the ambulance,
but he seems bad, like really bad.

24:58.623 --> 24:59.957
His breathing. His...

25:00.124 --> 25:02.460
- I think he punctured a lung.
- Fix it.

25:02.627 --> 25:05.546
- Are you like an EMT or something?
- Not exactly, sweetheart.

25:05.713 --> 25:09.300
- Oh, my God. We have to do something.
- Look, I can help, but... What's your name?

25:09.467 --> 25:11.636
- Sarah.
- Sarah. I need you to remain calm.

25:11.802 --> 25:14.972
What you're about to see
is something you've never seen before.

25:15.139 --> 25:18.601
- Just promise me you'll remain calm.
- I promise, just help him. Please.

25:21.604 --> 25:23.147
Oh, my God.

25:24.649 --> 25:25.816
Staying calm, love?

25:29.278 --> 25:31.405
[COUGHING]

25:31.572 --> 25:33.157
How did you just...?

25:35.368 --> 25:36.994
Did you ju...?

25:44.877 --> 25:45.962
There you are.

25:46.504 --> 25:50.091
- Oh, my God, what happened?
- Enzo's a dick, is what happened.

25:50.258 --> 25:53.928
Are you kidding me? Sit down.
I'm gonna kick his ass.

25:54.095 --> 25:58.641
I don't need my big sister beating up
bullies, thanks. What'd the sheriff want?

26:00.685 --> 26:03.563
She wanted to talk about the night
that Mom and Dad died.

26:04.855 --> 26:07.400
She thinks something else happened.

26:07.567 --> 26:09.652
Like maybe it wasn't an accident.

26:10.403 --> 26:11.529
Then what was it?

26:11.696 --> 26:15.575
A vampire attack? A werewolf on the road?
What else could we possibly go through?

26:15.741 --> 26:18.452
Mom had called her a couple of hours
before the crash.

26:18.619 --> 26:21.038
She left an urgent message
asking her to call back.

26:21.414 --> 26:25.543
Think. Do you remember anything
out of the ordinary about that night?

26:32.216 --> 26:33.676
What?

26:34.302 --> 26:37.722
I, uh, used to smoke pot in my room.

26:37.888 --> 26:39.181
Mom caught me that night.

26:39.348 --> 26:41.809
She said she was gonna have me arrested.

26:43.352 --> 26:45.688
So she called the sheriff.

26:45.855 --> 26:50.818
She was pretending to be all business,
but I could hear Jenna giggling outside.

26:52.445 --> 26:55.072
That was the last time we spoke...

26:56.866 --> 26:59.327
...fighting through a door.

27:01.329 --> 27:03.914
That makes sense.

27:04.081 --> 27:05.499
Yeah.

27:06.167 --> 27:07.918
I'll let her know.

27:13.090 --> 27:15.551
So the message was a joke.

27:17.345 --> 27:20.056
Miranda wanted you to bust Jeremy
for smoking pot.

27:22.516 --> 27:24.727
Well, what about everything else?

27:24.894 --> 27:28.731
I mean, the route, the skid marks.
What about the luggage?

27:29.190 --> 27:32.068
There was a storm the day before.

27:32.234 --> 27:35.237
Jeremy's dad was planning a secret trip
to their lake house...

27:35.404 --> 27:36.724
...and the storm rained them out.

27:36.947 --> 27:40.409
- The storm.
- Yeah.

27:40.618 --> 27:44.830
The storm that dropped a power line
across Old Miller Road...

27:44.997 --> 27:47.750
...explaining why they took
Wickery Bridge...

27:48.501 --> 27:51.837
...which had a drainage issue
before its renovation.

27:52.004 --> 27:54.924
Meaning the road was probably still slick.

27:55.091 --> 27:58.010
Slick roads, no skid marks.

27:58.177 --> 27:59.887
The storm.

28:01.013 --> 28:02.139
That was the reason.

28:04.308 --> 28:06.185
Mystery solved.

28:06.936 --> 28:08.354
[FORBES SIGHS]

28:10.481 --> 28:14.110
Would you mind calling Caroline and
telling her she can surprise me tomorrow?

28:14.276 --> 28:17.154
I'm not really feeling up to it tonight.

28:17.321 --> 28:18.989
Absolutely.

28:19.532 --> 28:20.616
I'll go get the car.

28:38.759 --> 28:40.344
[SIGHS]

29:19.300 --> 29:20.885
Yeah, thanks for letting me know.

29:21.051 --> 29:24.388
Just call me if there's
any other updates, okay? Bye.

29:25.681 --> 29:27.391
What happened? Sheriff okay?

29:29.894 --> 29:32.229
You weren't supposed to hear that.

29:32.980 --> 29:34.774
Damon said that she's getting worse.

29:35.608 --> 29:37.193
I can't leave now. No way.

29:37.359 --> 29:40.321
Not with the sheriff sick
and Enzo on a rampage.

29:40.488 --> 29:42.281
It's not the right time.

29:42.448 --> 29:44.909
No kidding. The right time
was a couple of years ago.

29:45.075 --> 29:46.395
Enzo could have killed you today.

29:46.702 --> 29:48.871
The other day,
Liv threw you across the room.

29:49.038 --> 29:51.248
Let's not forget the time
that you actually died.

29:51.415 --> 29:52.958
DAMON:
She's right.

29:53.125 --> 29:56.337
- Time to get the hell out of here.
- You deserve a normal life, Jer.

29:56.754 --> 30:01.884
You deserve the life of a kid whose only
baggage is that he lost his parents.

30:03.636 --> 30:07.264
Come on. Let's get you to the airport.

30:07.431 --> 30:11.268
Actually, why don't you let me take him?
You should go be with Liz.

30:11.435 --> 30:15.689
I'll call you when I get to the airport
and when I land.

30:18.734 --> 30:23.823
And in a couple days,
expect an SUV-sized package from me.

30:24.198 --> 30:27.159
- Hang on. You're giving me your car?
- Just don't crash it, okay?

30:36.669 --> 30:37.920
[SIGHS]

30:38.087 --> 30:39.255
DAMON:
Okay.

30:39.421 --> 30:40.589
Get in there.

30:41.674 --> 30:43.217
[FORBES SIGHS]

30:44.468 --> 30:48.055
Nice p.j. situation. You look hot.

30:48.222 --> 30:52.852
Ugh. I do not have the energy to tell you
how deeply that disturbs me.

30:57.565 --> 30:59.358
You wanted more today, didn't you?

31:00.359 --> 31:01.485
About the accident.

31:03.904 --> 31:08.951
If there had been a supernatural reason
they died, it would have been easier.

31:09.827 --> 31:11.328
It would have been a reason.

31:11.912 --> 31:14.164
As it is, it was just an accident.

31:16.292 --> 31:18.127
- Just a stupid accident.
- No.

31:19.211 --> 31:21.088
You wanted someone to blame.

31:24.925 --> 31:27.678
I did everything right, Damon.

31:29.305 --> 31:31.015
I lived a good life.

31:31.181 --> 31:33.517
I took care of my family.

31:33.684 --> 31:36.228
- I just...
- I know.

31:36.395 --> 31:39.857
Sometimes really terrible things happen
to really amazing people.

31:46.196 --> 31:50.701
I have to admit,
there is a certain amount of peace...

31:50.868 --> 31:56.165
...knowing I'll be one of the only people
in Mystic Falls to die an ordinary death.

31:56.332 --> 31:58.042
[CHUCKLES]

31:59.710 --> 32:01.587
I'm exceptionally ordinary.

32:03.339 --> 32:05.299
I'm okay with that.

32:05.925 --> 32:07.760
Caroline is anything but.

32:10.512 --> 32:13.557
She was meant to be extraordinary...

32:13.724 --> 32:16.143
...and she needs to know
how proud I am of her.

32:16.310 --> 32:17.478
Yeah. She will.

32:19.855 --> 32:21.190
You tell her yourself.

32:21.565 --> 32:23.025
Come on.

32:23.984 --> 32:25.235
Lay down on this bed.

32:34.912 --> 32:36.372
Thank you.

32:36.789 --> 32:38.040
For what?

32:39.500 --> 32:41.377
For today.

32:42.461 --> 32:43.837
For being here.

32:50.678 --> 32:54.348
Yeah, I didn't get a chance to spend
much time with my mom before she died.

32:57.017 --> 33:02.147
I volunteered to write the eulogy
and then when she actually died...

33:03.399 --> 33:05.818
...I didn't even go to the funeral.

33:09.989 --> 33:11.865
You want a second chance?

33:13.283 --> 33:14.535
DAMON:
Hm?

33:14.702 --> 33:15.995
Write mine.

33:17.997 --> 33:19.999
Only do me a favor, nothing dirty.

33:20.165 --> 33:21.542
No promises.

33:27.256 --> 33:28.841
[SIGHS]

33:31.510 --> 33:33.137
I'll take that drink now.

33:34.555 --> 33:35.931
Yeah?

33:37.808 --> 33:38.976
I'll be right back.

33:43.063 --> 33:45.357
You want rocks or you want neat?

33:51.280 --> 33:52.740
Liz?

33:54.366 --> 33:57.786
Where is she?
Elizabeth Forbes. What room is she in?

33:57.953 --> 33:59.872
- Caroline.
- Damon, what happened?

34:00.039 --> 34:03.584
She fell asleep. I couldn't wake her up.
They said she went into a coma.

34:08.338 --> 34:11.759
- They can make her comfortable.
- She's not comfortable. She's dying.

34:31.487 --> 34:34.114
I didn't get to say goodbye.

34:36.324 --> 34:39.495
I didn't get to say goodbye to my mom.

34:51.840 --> 34:54.467
Tyler, hey, it's Stefan.

34:54.635 --> 34:59.056
You might wanna head back to Mystic Falls.
Caroline's mom isn't doing too hot.

34:59.223 --> 35:01.391
I'll call you with updates.

35:03.852 --> 35:05.938
What'd the doctor say?

35:06.814 --> 35:10.067
Well, she's stable, but, you know...

35:11.193 --> 35:13.028
How much longer?

35:13.779 --> 35:17.032
Not long.
The hospital says she has a DNR, so...

35:20.869 --> 35:22.412
I'm gonna get some air.

35:34.007 --> 35:36.385
I should have been with her.

35:39.221 --> 35:40.389
You didn't know.

35:41.348 --> 35:43.809
But I knew she was sick.

35:44.685 --> 35:46.937
And I knew it was bad.

35:47.104 --> 35:49.439
- Caroline...
- I'm her daughter, Stefan.

35:50.524 --> 35:53.610
Okay? I was supposed to give her peace...

35:53.944 --> 35:56.780
...and convince her that I would be okay...

35:56.947 --> 36:02.077
...and thank her for being an amazing mom.

36:02.870 --> 36:07.249
God, I don't even remember the last thing
that I said to her.

36:08.750 --> 36:12.629
I was supposed to be with her
in her final moment.

36:16.758 --> 36:18.719
You still can.

36:31.231 --> 36:32.482
[ALARIC GROANS]

36:32.649 --> 36:34.109
Oh, yeah.

36:34.276 --> 36:35.611
Airport looks packed.

36:36.069 --> 36:38.572
Yeah. Long-ass security line too.

36:45.495 --> 36:47.247
I don't want you to miss your flight.

36:47.414 --> 36:49.416
I know you have orientation tomorrow.

36:50.626 --> 36:54.338
Look, this probably goes without saying,
but you keep this shut...

36:55.464 --> 36:58.258
...till you get off the bus.
Just stuff that above your seat.

36:59.343 --> 37:01.470
This is where you're headed.

37:01.637 --> 37:04.514
The bus will take you to an old town
about 30 miles north of Santa Fe.

37:04.681 --> 37:08.185
Now, I can't confirm if these were
actual animal attacks or something else...

37:08.352 --> 37:10.270
- ...but it's worth looking into.
- I'm on it.

37:10.437 --> 37:14.149
You're probably gonna have to generate
some art to actually sell the story.

37:14.316 --> 37:18.654
If Elena finds out this is a big lie, she's not
gonna just kill you, she's gonna kill me too.

37:19.112 --> 37:20.530
Yeah. Elena will be fine...

37:20.697 --> 37:23.200
- ...as long as she thinks that I'm safe.
- And happy.

37:26.036 --> 37:30.540
You know, a responsible guardian
would try and stop you.

37:31.458 --> 37:32.584
- But?
- Believe it or not...

37:32.751 --> 37:34.336
...you're actually an adult now.

37:34.503 --> 37:39.341
And you found your purpose,
so you might as well pursue it.

37:40.342 --> 37:43.345
Granted, being a vampire hunter
doesn't lend itself to a social life.

37:43.512 --> 37:47.474
Yeah, it turns out a social life
isn't as much fun as kicking vampire ass.

37:47.641 --> 37:49.351
Just don't do anything stupid, okay?

37:49.935 --> 37:52.229
Now, I'll send you leads,
you can follow up on them.

37:52.396 --> 37:55.148
We already went over this.
Nobody needs to worry about me, okay?

37:58.485 --> 38:01.154
It's not like I'm not gonna have e-mail
or anything.

38:01.321 --> 38:02.823
Just shut up. Let me hug you.

38:08.495 --> 38:09.871
I'm proud of you, Jeremy.

38:12.165 --> 38:13.542
Hey, do me a favor.

38:13.875 --> 38:16.920
- If Bonnie ever comes back...
- You'll be the first person I call.

38:53.040 --> 38:54.833
Try to clear your mind.

38:55.000 --> 38:56.668
Okay.

38:58.378 --> 39:02.424
Think about your favorite memory
of your mom.

39:02.591 --> 39:04.259
I don't know. There's too many.

39:04.426 --> 39:06.762
It's okay. It's okay.

39:06.928 --> 39:08.555
Just relax.

39:08.722 --> 39:13.060
Close your eyes, open up your mind.

39:13.518 --> 39:16.104
We're gonna live in her memories.

39:16.646 --> 39:18.273
We can do that?

39:20.901 --> 39:22.778
Just take her hand.

39:44.966 --> 39:46.843
YOUNG CAROLINE:
Mom, I want to stop.

39:47.010 --> 39:49.846
FORBES:
<i>If you stop, you'll never learn, sweetie.</i>

39:50.472 --> 39:51.952
YOUNG CAROLINE:
I don't want to learn.

39:52.099 --> 39:53.600
FORBES:
Yes, you do.

39:53.767 --> 39:55.227
YOUNG CAROLINE:
<i>I can't do it.</i>

39:55.394 --> 39:57.646
FORBES:
<i>Just pedal.</i>

39:59.940 --> 40:01.024
I'm gonna fall.

40:01.191 --> 40:03.777
I'm holding you up, sweetheart.
You can't fall.

40:04.319 --> 40:05.654
I'm scared.

40:05.821 --> 40:08.156
I want my other wheels back on.

40:12.119 --> 40:13.787
It's working.

40:17.416 --> 40:19.835
Keep pedaling. You can do it.

40:20.001 --> 40:22.462
- Don't let go, Mommy.
- I won't.

40:22.629 --> 40:23.880
Not till you're ready.

40:24.047 --> 40:26.508
Don't let go. I'm not ready.

40:36.643 --> 40:38.979
Yes, you are.

41:13.054 --> 41:14.806
[MONITOR BEEPING]

41:14.973 --> 41:16.057
[SOFTLY]
Mom.

41:18.852 --> 41:20.645
Mom.

41:28.403 --> 41:30.572
She's gone.

41:32.199 --> 41:34.242
[CAROLINE SOBBING]

41:48.381 --> 41:49.799
[BEEPING STOPS]

42:20.205 --> 42:22.207
[English - US - SDH]
